    {
      "id": "b2ae352a_ade6cc60",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/components/so-monitoring/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 30,
      "message": "for the other merged code, it's code that was already there I guess or it's an error\nSpring allows you to use ENV variable as far as I can tell.\nAnd having \"encrypted\" it is neither secure or sufficient.\n\nSo as you want (need?) to have it encrypted, you need to provide the unencrypted value (preferably auto generated for the password part) in a secret and use an init container to encrypt it and set it in your override file.\nthere's a lot of examples (https://github.com/onap/oom/blob/master/kubernetes/aaf/components/aaf-sms/templates/job.yaml) on how to subsitute environment values into config files but you'll also need to encrypt them in a previous init container I guess.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2319,
        "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
        "username": "sdesbure"
      },
      "updated": "2020-10-21 06:46:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d15a168c_2cddfc50",
      "unresolved": true
    },
